
'''Oxford Media Convention 2006: Rights and revenue models: what IP model for public service communications?'''

URL = http://webcast.oii.ox.ac.uk/?view=Webcast&ID=20060119_115


=Speakers=


Chair: Will Davies, ippr associate


Sara Geater, head of commercial affairs, Channel 4
Paul Gerhardt, project director, Creative Archive, BBC
Andrew Yeates, legal adviser, The Educational Recording Agency


=Summary=


Intellectual property rights are one of the most fiercely contested areas of policy in the digital age. This panel will look at ways of balancing different interests between rights-holders, creators, public institutions and consumers. Areas to be explored will include the BBC's Creative Archive, the interests of independent producers and creators, and new revenue models suitable for the internet.

